properties.description: Posted by Baobot 930 Lincoln Street, Denver, CO, United StatesDazzle Jazz ::: Live Music Every Night! Original Photo ?? Ned Radinsky courtesy rockymountainjazz.com Dazzle Restaurant & Lounge presents an authentic Jazz Club experience unlike anything in Colorado. We pride ourselves on the high quality of service, food, and drink while providing an intimate showcase of local, national, and international musicians. Named ??One of the Top 100 Jazz Club in the World? by Downbeat magazine and ??Best Jazz Club? by The Westword, we strive to be a positive and unique part of the Denver community. Dazzle features a unique and eclectic menu that focuses on the great American traditional cuisine with a twist. We cater to a wide variety of tastes with entrees ranging from burgers and pizza to our Beer Battered Cod or Grilled Buffalo Chopped Steak. We also boast a happy-hour menu running early-evenings and late-nights. We feature live performances in both our lounge and dining room, seven nights a week. The dining room is designed with the jazz listener in mind, featuring acoustically treated walls and optimal seating. The performances are front and center, and are not treated as background music. Our lounge sports a comfortable neighborhood atmosphere and is also acoustically treated for the best possible aural experience. The bar serves a large assortment of Martinis, Manhattans, and classic cocktails, as well as wine and beer. Dazzle is also available for private parties and corporate events! Come to Dazzle and enjoy our fine food, classy cocktails, sincere service, and the best Jazz in Denver! Current e-mail blast - click here! We have Reserved Parking for our patrons. Our lots are up the alley, just north of the Dazzle. The parking garages attached to our building are for the residents and are therefore not for Dazzle patrons. properties.name: Uptown Tavern
properties.description: Posted by Josephine 523 E 17th Ave, Denver, COSteuben’s is named after a restaurant in Boston that opened in 1945. Steubens became a famous Boston restaurant, nightclub, and hotspot from the 1940’s to the 1960’s on Boylston Street. The Vienna Room, The Cave, and The Blue Room were all part of the Steubens space and hosted Big Bands, Jazz Bands, Swing Bands, The Rat Pack, Proms and Sweet Sixteens. In its prime, Steuben’s was the center of the Boston dining and nightlife scene. Steubens, Denver, is a restaurant that respects the history of its name and the core ingredients of the American Regional classics we have attempted to recreate. These dishes are America’s cuisine and American’s interpretations of the dishes of our diverse cultural heritage. We have enjoyed the endless debates, opinions, stories, research, consultations and food memories that have led us to the opening version of the Steuben’s menu. Eat at Steuben’s. Take-Out from Steuben’s. Drink at Steuben’s. Feel at home, in Denver, at Steuben’s.

Even omnivores swear by the flavorful, eclectic cooking that comes out of the Watercourse kitchen, especially the seitan parmesan and the fettucine puttanesca. WHAT TO GET: Come for breakfast and get a scramble
